  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators conducted a prospective randomized study to compare axillary
      minithoracotomy versus a modified two-port thoracoscopic technique for surgical pleurodesis
      in patients with recurrent spontaneous pneumothorax operated in a single institution.

      The main objective of the study was to investigate possible differences regarding short- and
      long-term clinical outcome between the two different techniques.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
